               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-199-person1715">
                  SAMUEL 
                  FURZEMAN
               <interp inst="t18190915-199-person1715" type="surname" value="FURZEMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-199-person1715" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-199-person1715" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner's in company with another in Drury-lane, following a gentleman. I followed them through Broad-court; they continually attempted the gentleman's pocket - they drew up close behind him in Plumtree-court. In a moment I saw Davis turn, and run down the court, doubling something under his apron - the other two passed the gentleman. I followed Davis, laid hold of him in Broad-street, and found the handkerchief under his apron. I took him into Plumbtree-street, and called the gentleman who claimed it. The gentleman is gone to Ireland - my brother secured Hendrick. The gentleman's name was 
               <persName id="t18190915-199-person1716">
                  Henry 
                  Longman
               <interp inst="t18190915-199-person1716" type="surname" value="Longman"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-199-person1716" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
